1 mdx
2 h2 Artifact
3 p An artifact is a set of descriptors used to instantiate and execute an artifact production (alias generation process).
4 ul Artifact descriptors
5 li Main source model
6 li Context models
7 li Generation module
8 li Transpilers
9 li Destination path
10 h3 Main source model
11 p The main source module can be a wizzi model or a POJO passed to a 'wizzi-plugin.artifactGenerator.gen' method in the 'model' parameter.
12 h3 Context models
13 p Context models are wizzi models or POJO passed to a 'wizzi-plugin.artifactGenerator.gen' method in the 'values' object property of the 'ctx' (api-ref: wizzi.artifact.genContext) parameter. The name of each context model, defeined in the 'export-name' attribute of the 'modelRef' element of the 'wfjob' model, is a property name of the 'values' object.
14 h3 Generation module
15 p Is a nodejs module that implements the 'wizzi-plugin.artifactGenerator' interface. It uses the main source model and optionally the context models to generate the textual artifact. The artifact is buffered using the 'write' and 'w' methods of the 'wizzi.artifact.genContext' instance, but the code text can be built using the services of the wizzi factory and its language schemas and language artifacts. The current instance of the wizzi.wizziFactory class can be accessed from 'wizzi-plugin.artifactGenerator' implementors in the property 'wizziFactory' of the 'wizzi.artifact.genContext' instance.
16 h3 Transpilers
17 p A transpiler is a nodejs module that implements the wizzi-plugin.transpiler interface.
18 h3 Destination path
19 p A destination path is the location where a generated artifact is persisted.
20 h2 Artifact types
21 ul
22 li Model artifact
23 li Model collection artifact
24 li Code write artifact
25 li Final artifact
26 h3 Model artifact
27 p A model artifact is an artifact which main source model is a wizzi model.
28 h3 Model collection artifact
29 p A model collection artifact is a model artifact which source model is an item of a collection property of a wizzi model. The same artifact is applied to all the items of the collection and generates distinct code units, for any of them, which file path is built using a template interpolated with the values of the item properties.
30 h3 Code write artifact
31 p A code write artifact do not require a wizzi model as a main source model. The artifact generator receive in the 'model' parameter a context object, which properties are the items of the context models collection. It emits the code using the 'write' and 'w' methods of a wizzi.artifact,genContext instance.
32 h3 Native artifact
33 p A native artifact is a source already coded in the synthax of a target language. It is not processed by the wizzi factory. It can be copied as is in the destination folder or can be transpiled before copying.

3 #
4 # Objects
5 # - Model
6 # Is the core object of the model driven wizzi factory.
7 # A model is a single object (wizzi model or POJO) acting as a context object in
8 # mTree loadings, model transformations and artifact generations.
9 # Models (single or group of similars) are described by wizzi.model.modelInfo api.
10 # - Templated model
11 # A templated model is a model that contains itself template commands and require
12 # one or more context objects. The process is recursive and has no limit except
13 # a guard to avoid infinite loops during recursive evaluation of contexts.
14 # - Context models
15 # Context models are an array of models acting as a context object for a templated
16 # model.
17 # Context models, being models themselves, are also described by wizzi.model.modelInfo api.
18 # - Model collection
19 # A model collection is an array property of a model, where each item of
20 # the array is used as a model acting as a context object.
21 # The properties of the item can be used to build the destination path of the generated artifact.
22 # Model collections are described in the wizzi.model.ModelCollectionInfo api.
23 # TODO Implement transformModel context objects.

26 # The wizzi.productionManager is used for complex productions.
27 # It executes wfjob models.
28 #
29 #
30 # The 'meat' of a production is the execution of a wizzi.artifact.artifactInfo instance
31 # performed by an instance of a wizzi.production.Runner.
32 # wizzi.artifact.artifactInfo (s) are added to the wizzi.production.productionManager
33 # in three ways:
34 # 1. adding a request for loading a 'wfjob' wizzi model.
35 # 2. adding a wfjobArtifactModel
36 # 3. adding a wizzi.artifact.artifactInfo created programmaticaly.
37 # When the 'run' method is called the production manager:
38 # 1. loads the requested wfjobModels.
39 # A wfjobModel can contain wfjobArtifactModel(s) and others 'wfjob' requests.
40 # Every wfjob request is execute until we have wfjobArtifactModel(s) only.
41 # 2 wfjobArtifactModel(s) are transformed in instances of wizzi.artifact.artifactInfo (s)
42 # 3 A wizzi.production.Runner is instantiated and asynchronously executed for each
43 # wizzi.artifact.artifactInfo.
44 #
45 # addArtifactInfo(artifactInfo)
46 # addWfJob(wfJobConfig)
47 # getLoadModel(schemaName)
48 # getWizziSchemaObject(schemaName)
49 # getModelTransformer(transName)
50 # getArtifactGenerator(artifactName)
51 # run:AsyncMethod

1 mdx
2 h2 Production
3 h3 The wizzi.production.productionManager
4 p Manages a production of software artifacts. It is instantiated by a wizzi.wizziFactory instance which sets up the production environment (plugins, global context, store system). Clients use its 'addJobRequest' and 'addArtifactRequest' methods to add artifact requests and then use the 'run' and 'persistToFile' methods to execute the generations and save to file the generated artifacts.
5 h3 The wizzi.production.wfjobLoader
6 p Async load a 'wfjob' wizzi model and accumulate wfjobArtifactModel elements. If the model contains 'wfjob' requests also check that they have not already been processed and add them to pendingWfjobRequests. If the model contains wfjobArtifactModel elements check that they have not already been added and add them to the artifactInfoConfigs collection.
7 h3 The wizzi.production.runner
8 p Executes the generations described by a wizzi.artifact.artifactInfo instance. It is instantiated by the wizzi.production.productionManager, selects the artifact type, and asynchronously run the generations using the wizzi.artifact.asyncArtifactGenerator.
9 p The generated artifacts are added to the 'genContexts' collection of the wizzi.artifact.artifactInfo instance.
10 h3 The wizzi.production.persister
11 p Executes the write to file of the generated artifacts added to the 'genContexts' collection of a wizzi.artifact.artifactInfo instance. It is instantiated by the wizzi.production.productionManager, and asynchronously executes the writes using the wizzi.production.asyncArtifactFilePersister.
12 h3 The global context
13 p The default value in options.js is empty ( = {} )
14 p The user can pass a global context to
15 ul
16 li A wizzi job execution
17 li An mTree load
18 li A wizzi model load
19 li An artifact generation
20 span using the property globalContext of the options parameter of
21 ul
22 li The wizzi.executeInstanceJob method
23 li The wizzi.createFactory method
24 p Creating a wizziFactory instance always is preliminar to executing an mTree load, a wizzi model load or an artifact generation.
25 p The wizzi.executeInstanceJob creates its wizziFactory instance from the options that receives.

1 mdx
2 h2 The wizzi.WizziFactory class
3 p All wizzi factory operations require an instance of the wizzi.WizziFactory class.
4 ul A wizzi.WizziFactory instance manages
5 li The store system (filesystem, mongodb or localstorage).
6 li The global context.
7 li The loading of plugins.
8 h3 The store system
9 p The store system is set at creation time and cannot be changed.
10 h3 The global context
11 p The global context is set at creation time and cannot be changed.
12 h3 The loading of plugins
13 p Plugins are loaded at creation time and cannot be changed.
14 h3 Operations
15 ul
16 li mTree loading
17 li Wizzi model loading
18 li Model transformation
19 li Artifact generation
20 li Wizzi model types generation
21 li Production manager creation
22 li Wizzi job execution
23 h3 mTree loading
24 p Executes the loading of an mTree from an ittf document.
25 h3 Wizzi model loading
26 p Executes the loading, initialization and validation of a wizzi model from an ittf document.
27 p TODO the 'modelContext' paramater can contain properties of type wizzi.model.modelInfo. wizzi.model.modelInfo(s) will be resolved and replaced with the loaded wizzi models.
28 h3 Model transformation
29 p Executes the transformation of a wizzi model or POJO.
30 h3 Artifact generation
31 p Executes the generation of a single software artifact.
32 h3 Wizzi model types generation
33 p The generation of the javascript modules for loading and implement a wizzi model is a fundamental part of a wizzi plugin development.
34 p A wizzi model of type 'wfschema' describes a wizzi model and its constraints. The method 'generateModelTypes' of the wizzi.wizziFactory uses a 'wfschema' model to generate the javascript artifacts that implement a wizzi model.
35 h3 Wizzi job execution
36 p A wizzi job is described by a wizzi model of schema 'wfjob', that can contain artifact production requests and optional references to other 'wfjob' models. The 'executeJob' method of the wizzi.wizziFactory triggers the loading of a 'wfjob' model, the resolution of the references to other 'wfjob' models and the execution of the requested artifact productions.
37 h3 Production manager creation
38 p An instance of a wizzi.production.productionManager class allow a more fine grained control on artifact productions. To a wizzi.production.productionManager instance we can add wizzi job requests ( 'addJobRequest' method ) and single artifact requests ( 'addArtifactRequest' method ), then we can execute the run method and obtain wizzi.artifact.genContexts filled with the artifact ready to be persisted, and, at the end, we can execute the 'persistToFile' method.
